# User Story: Similarity Check for Duplicate Rule Detection

-----

**US-001: Warn user of similar existing rules before creating a new rule**

**As a** data governance user,  
**I want to** be warned when a rule I am writing for a data element is similar to an existing rule,  
**So that** I do not create duplicate rules, even if I phrase them differently from the original.

-----

## Acceptance Criteria

```gherkin
Feature: Similarity check against existing rules for a data element

  Background:
    Given the rule catalogue contains the following rules for the "Customer Email" data element:
      | id     | rule                                                   |
      | DQ-001 | Customer email address must not be null                |
      | DQ-002 | Email is required for every customer record            |

  Scenario: User writes a rule that is semantically similar to an existing rule
    When the user enters the rule "The email field for a customer cannot be empty"
    Then the system checks the new rule against existing rules for "Customer Email"
    And returns a warning "A similar rule already exists"
    And displays the matching rule [DQ-001] with its similarity score
    And prevents the rule from being saved without user acknowledgement

  Scenario: User writes a rule that is not similar to any existing rule
    When the user enters the rule "Customer email domain must be from an approved list"
    Then the system checks the new rule against existing rules for "Customer Email"
    And no similar rules are found
    And the rule is saved successfully

  Scenario: User acknowledges the warning and chooses to save anyway
    When the user enters the rule "The email field for a customer cannot be empty"
    And the system warns that [DQ-001] is similar
    And the user confirms they want to save the rule despite the warning
    Then the rule is saved with a note that a similar rule exists

  Scenario: User acknowledges the warning and cancels the save
    When the user enters the rule "The email field for a customer cannot be empty"
    And the system warns that [DQ-001] is similar
    And the user cancels the save
    Then no new rule is created
    And the user is returned to the rule creation screen
```
